# Regression: same-output overloaded builtins used directly as `iff`
# branches. `cd` and `toPath` are overloaded on str|path, but every arm
# shares an output, so a quote like `(cd)` / `(toPath cd)` now infers as
# a single union-input (plain) quote and is accepted as a branch.
# Previously these failed type-checking with "no matching overload for
# 'iff'" because the quote inferred as an overloaded quote.
#
# Run by both typecheck_test.sh (the type-check is the feature under
# test) and test.sh (the program must also execute and print "ok").

# Condition true runs the first branch, dropping the pwd path.
pwd true (drop) (cd) iff
# Condition false runs the second branch: cd to the current dir (a no-op
# at runtime), exercising the overloaded `(cd)` branch quote.
pwd false (drop) (cd) iff
# `(toPath cd)` composes two overloaded ops in one branch quote.
pwd false (drop) (toPath cd) iff

"ok" wl
